# {{.Name}} (jughead site plugin)

A site plugin generated by `jughead init`.

## Build

The plugin must be built with the **same Go toolchain and dependency versions**
as the host jughead binary, because Go's `plugin` package requires byte-identical
type identities across the `.so` boundary.

```
CGO_ENABLED=1 go build -buildmode=plugin -o {{.Name}}.so .
```

## Run standalone (iterate without the full host)

```
jughead serve ./{{.Name}}.so --port 8080
```

## Run inside the full host

Set `JUGHEAD_PLUGINS_DIR` to the directory containing `{{.Name}}.so` and start
jughead. The site registers under `{{.SitePath}}`.

## Files

- `plugin.go` — declares the `Plugin` symbol the host loads.
- `main_stub.go` — no-op main so `go build` works without `-buildmode=plugin`.
- `go.mod` — pins the jughead version. Keep it in sync with the host.